==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Self-contradiction
<hw>Self`-con`tra*dic"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act
of contradicting one's self or itself; repugnancy in conceptions or in
terms; a proposition consisting of two members, one of which contradicts
the other; <as>as, to be and not to be at the same time is a
<ex>self-contradiction</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Self-contradictory</ent>⟦br⟧
